            <title>[DERBY-1159] PreparedStatement.executeUpdate throws a XJ05C exception in a global transaction if the statement is HOLD_CURSORS_OVER_COMMIT</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1159</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SQLSTATE(XJ05C): Cannot set holdability ResultSet.HOLD_CURSORS_OVER_COMMIT for&lt;br/&gt;
 a global transaction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Exception is thrown in client, in embedded the statement executes successfully.&lt;br/&gt;
Since HOLD_CURSORS_OVER_COMMIT  only applies to ResultSets  and executeUpdate states it only succeeds if the statement&lt;br/&gt;
does not generate ResultSets, then this combination should succeed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Probably related to the fact that in embedded an execute() call on the same PreparedStatement will thrown a  XJ05C exception&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Workaround is to prepare the statement explicitly with CLOSE_CURSORS_AT_COMMIT.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
